<DOC><DOCNO> AP890802-0208 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-08-02-89 2332EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Guatemala-Drugs     08-02 0141</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Guatemala-Drugs,0146</SECOND><HEAD>Anti-Corruption Official Arrested on Drug Charges</HEAD><DATELINE>GUATEMALA CITY (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   An official of the government'santi-corruption agency was arrested when he allegedly tried toboard a Miami-bound flight with 97 pounds of cocaine in hisluggage, police said Wednesday.   Jose Fernando Minero Navas, 27, was arrested at theinternational airport,   National Police spokesman Guillermo Mollinedo said.   The spokesman said Minero worked at the airport as an agent ofthe Presidential Department of Administrative Control, which wascreated by President Vinicio Cerezo's administration to fightofficial corruption. The unit at the airport handled agencies likecustoms and immigration.   Mollinedo said Minero was arrested Tuesday after police becamesuspicious of what appeared to be unusually heavy hand luggage. Hesaid police inspected the bag and found about 97 pounds of cocaine.   Drug charges have been filed against Minero, he said.</TEXT></DOC>